# Sync Home Assistant config to the live share

Edits under `homeassistant/` (root YAML, `automations/`, `dashboards/`, `packages/`, `www/`, `blueprints/`) are **not** read by Home Assistant until they exist on the HA host (`/config`). This repo treats **`\\192.168.89.25\config`** as that live tree (Samba).

**After changing any file matched by the globs above, run from the repo root:**

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/sync_homeassistant_config.ps1
```

(PowerShell 7: `pwsh -File ...`.) Use another path only if the share moves: `-ConfigRoot '\\other\config'`.

Do **not** consider the task done for dashboard/package work until this script has been run successfully (or the user confirms they deploy another way).
